<div class="container">
    <h2 class="heading">Susan's Bio:</h2>
    <p class="lead">
        Susan Davis resides in Inman, SC, and is a native of the area.  She received her Master of Music in Piano Pedagogy from Converse College in 2006, where she studied with Melanie Foster Taylor.  Prior to graduate work, Susan received her Bachelor of Arts in Music, piano, from Converse College in 1990 and an Associates in Arts from Spartanburg Methodist College in 1987.  In 1989, Susan studied with Rita Sloan at the Aspen Music Festival in Aspen, Colorado.  She has also studied piano with John Erickson, Professor Emeritus Converse College, Richard Cass, SC Governor's School for the Arts, and Hao Huang, and Melanie Foster Taylor, both at Converse College.
    </p>
    <p class="lead">
        In 2004-2005, Susan participated in master classes with Menahem Pressler of the Beaux Arts Trio and Kenneth Drake.  In addition to performing in benefit concerts for Tsunami and Hurricane Katrina victims, she also performed in the All Steinway Celebration at Converse College.  Susan is a member of the Rho Chapter of Pi Kappa Lambda, a National Music Honors Society, the South Carolina Music Teachers Association and the Asheville Area Piano Forum.  Susan regularly performs in solo and duo recitals and presents piano music programs for various civic and community organizations as well.
    </p>
    <p class="lead">
        From 2000-2007, Susan taught piano at Spartanburg Methodist College along with a private studio for 30 years.  Susan teaches Applied Piano, Group Piano, Music History and Introduction to Music at The University of South Carolina Upstate and Music Appreciation at Spartanburg Community College.  In addition, she maintains her private piano studio.
    </p>
